## Key Takeaways

By the end of this course, I was able to:
- Explain core cybersecurity concepts and terminology.
- Identify common cyber threats and attack methods.
- Differentiate between various threat actors and their motivations.
- Understand how security frameworks and compliance standards reduce organizational risk.
- Recognize the ethical and legal responsibilities of cybersecurity professionals.
- Describe the purpose of commonly used security tools and technologies.

